         <div type="interview">
            <head>Interview with T.H. Ziegler and Detectives</head>
            <byline>Amanda Woertz</byline>

            <p><persName key="allen" ref ='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>Coroner's</persName> Inquest <objectName type="document"
                  >Transcript</objectName></p>

            <p>The following is the <objectName>transcript</objectName> of the <objectName
                  type="document">shorthand notes</objectName> taken at the <persName key="allen" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'
                  >Coroner's</persName>
               <eventName type="case">inquest</eventName> held on the <objectName key="taylor" ref ='#director'
                  >body</objectName> of <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>William Desmond Taylor</persName> at
                     <placeName><orgName>Ivy H. Overholtzer</orgName> [Mortuary]</placeName> at
                  <placeName>Los Angeles, California</placeName> on the <date>4th day of February,
                  1922 </date>at <time>10:00 a.m</time>. </p>
            <p><persName key="ziegler" ref ='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>T.H. Ziegler</persName>, being first duly sworn, <eventName
                  type="case">testified</eventName> as follows:</p>

            <p>BY THE CORONER:</p>

            <p>NANCE: Please state your name.</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: <persName key="ziegler" ref ='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>T.H. Ziegler</persName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Where do you live?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: <placeName type="address">425 North Hill</placeName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: What is your <orgName type="job">occupation</orgName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: <orgName type="job">Police officer</orgName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: <persName key="ziegler" ref ='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>Mr. Ziegler</persName>, were you called to the
                  <placeName type="house">premises</placeName> when the <objectName key="taylor"
                  >deceased</objectName> was <eventName type="evidence">found dead</eventName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: I was.</p>

            <p>NANCE: When did you arrive <placeName type="house">there</placeName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: A little <time>before</time>
               <time>8 o'clock</time> in the <time>morning</time> of <date>February 2nd</date>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Will you state what you found when you got <placeName type="house"
                  >there</placeName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: I found the <objectName key="taylor">deceased</objectName>, <persName
                  key="taylor" ref='#director'>Mr. Taylor</persName>, lying just <placeName type="house"
                  >inside</placeName> of the <objectName type="passage">door</objectName>, on
                  <persName key="taylor" ref ='#director'>his</persName>
               <objectName type="bodyPart">back</objectName>. <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>His</persName>
               <objectName type="bodyPart">hands</objectName>, one of them, apparently to the side
               of <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>his</persName>
               <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>body</persName>, and the other lying outstretched; and
                  <objectName type="bodyPart">blood</objectName> pouring from <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'
                  >his</persName>
               <objectName type="bodyPart">mouth</objectName>. <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>He</persName>
               was lying with <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>his</persName>
               <objectName type="bodyPart">head</objectName> to the <placeName type="direction"
                  >east</placeName>, flat on <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>his</persName>
               <objectName type="bodyPart">back</objectName>, dead. </p>
            <p>NANCE: Was <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>his</persName>
               <objectName key="taylor">body</objectName> rigid and cold?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: It was.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Indicating <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>he</persName> had been dead for <time>some
                  time</time>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: Yes, <persName key="nance" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>sir</persName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did you see any <objectName type="evidence">evidence</objectName> of a disturbance
               in the <placeName type="house">house</placeName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: Not any.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Who was <placeName type="house">there</placeName> when you arrived <placeName
                  type="house">there</placeName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: The <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business'>owner</persName> of the <objectName
                  type="building">building</objectName>; <persName key="dougMacLean" ref='#actor' role ='social'>Mr.
                  MacLean</persName>; another <persName key="maigne" ref='#actor' role ='social'>movie actor</persName>
                  [<persName key="maigne" ref='#actor' role ='social'>Charles Maigne</persName>], and <persName key="peavey" ref='#servant' role = 'social'
                  >Peavey</persName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: You mean the <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business'>owner</persName> of the <objectName
                  type="building">building</objectName>, <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role ='business'>Mr.
                  Jessurun</persName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: Yes, <persName key="nance" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>sir</persName>, and <persName key="dougMacLean" ref='#actor' role ='social'
                  >Mr. MacLean</persName> and another <persName>man</persName> I don't know.</p>

            <p>NANCE: One of the <placeName type="location">adjacent</placeName>
               <persName key="tenants" role ='social'>tenants </persName>of the <objectName type="building"
                  >building</objectName>?</p>

            <p> ZIEGLER: Yes <persName key="nance" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>sir</persName>, living <placeName type="location"
                  >next <objectName type="passage">door</objectName></placeName>
               <placeName type="direction">east</placeName> of <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>Mr.
                  Taylor</persName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did you <eventName type="case">question</eventName> any of those <persName
                  key="tenants" role = 'social'>persons</persName> as to whether they had heard any gunshot the
                  <time>night previous</time>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: I did. I learned that from <persName key="faithMacLean" ref='#actor'>Mrs.
                  MacLean</persName>, that along about <time>fifteen or perhaps ten minutes to
                  eight,</time>
               <time>the night before</time>, <persName key="faithMaclean" ref='#actor' role ='social' >she</persName> heard
                  <objectName type="gun">a shot</objectName>. <persName key="faithMacLean" ref='#actor' role ='social'
                  >She</persName> thought it was a gunshot. <persName key="faithMacLean" ref='#actor' role ='social'
                  >She</persName> went to <persName key="faithMacLean" ref='#actor' role ='social'>her</persName>
               <placeName type="passage">front door</placeName> and opened the <objectName
                  type="passage">door</objectName>, and saw a <persName key="murderer" role = 'unknown'
                  >man</persName> standing in <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>Mr. Taylor's</persName>
               <objectName type="passage">door</objectName>. <persName key="faithMacLean" ref='#actor' role ='social'
                  >She</persName> looked at <persName key="murderer">him</persName>, and <persName
                  key="murderer" role ='unknown'>he</persName> stood and looked at <persName key="faithMacLean" ref='#actor' role ='social'
                  >her</persName>; and <persName key="murderer" role ='unkown'>he</persName> walked down the
                  <objectName type="passage">steps</objectName>, turned to the left, and going
               around the <placeName type="building">end of the building</placeName>, which is to
               the <placeName type="location">east</placeName>; and out into the <objectName
                  type="passage">street</objectName>. </p>
            <p>NANCE: Into what <objectName type="passage">street</objectName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: Which is <placeName type="street"> Maryland</placeName>, I think.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business'>Mr. Jessurun</persName> tell you <persName
                  key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business'>he</persName> heard <objectName type="gun">a shot</objectName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: I think <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business' >he</persName> did.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business' >he</persName> say why <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business' 
                  >he</persName> didn't try to investigate it?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business' >He</persName> did not. <persName key="jessurun" ref='#professional' role = 'business'
                  >He</persName> didn't know but what it was an <objectName type="vehicle"
                  >automobile</objectName> making a noise.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did <persName key="dougMacLean" ref='#actor' role = 'social' >Mr. MacLean</persName> endeavor to investigate
               it?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: Not that I know of, and <persName key="maid" ref= '#servant' role ='unknonw'>Mrs. MacLean's maid</persName>
               also heard <objectName type="gun">a shot</objectName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did <persName>they</persName> say why <persName>they</persName> didn't attempt
               to investigate the cause of the <objectName type="gun">shot</objectName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: <persName>They</persName> did not.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did you find any <objectName type="gun">weapon</objectName> about
                  the<placeName type="house">room</placeName> where the <objectName key="taylor"
                  >deceased</objectName> was lying?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: I found a <objectName type="gun"> weapon</objectName> in the <placeName
                  type="house">room</placeName> above.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Where was it?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: In the <placeName type="house">front bedroom</placeName> in the <objectName
                  type="furniture">dresser drawer</objectName>, lying on a sort of <objectName
                  type="furniture">box</objectName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did you <eventName type="case">investigate</eventName> to see whether the
                  <objectName type="clothing">clothing</objectName> was <objectName>powder
                  burnt</objectName> or not?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: I did not. That was <eventName type="investigaton">investigated</eventName>,
               I understand, <time>later</time>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Did you ask any of the <persName>persons</persName> who were called by
                  <persName key="peavy" ref='#servant' role = 'unknown'>Henry Peavey, the valet</persName>, whether there was any
                  <objectName type="gun">weapon</objectName> there when they first came into the
                  <placeName type="house">room</placeName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: Yes, <persName key="nance" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>sir</persName>. We looked for everything of that
               kind.</p>

            <p>NANCE: Have you formed any <eventName type="case">conclusion</eventName> whether it
               was possible this <objectName type="gun">shot</objectName> could have been fired by
               the <objectName key="taylor">deceased</objectName>
               <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>himself</persName>?</p>
            <p>ZIEGLER: Impossible.</p>

            <p>THE CORONER: Have you any questions, gentlemen?</p>

            <p>NANCE: By a <persName key="juror" ref='#legal' role ='unknown'>juror</persName>: Was the <objectName type="gun"
                  >revolver</objectName> found <placeName type="location">upstairs</placeName>
               <objectName type="gun">loaded</objectName>? </p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: It was. It had five <objectName type="gun">shells</objectName> in it; it had
               not been shot of <time>late</time>. </p>

            <p>NANCE: Was it the same caliber <objectName type="gun">bullet</objectName> as was
               found on the <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>deceased</persName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: This was a <objectName type="gun">.32 automatic Savage</objectName>.</p>

            <p>NANCE: In the <objectName type="furniture">drawer</objectName>
               <placeName type="location">upstairs</placeName>?</p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: Yes.</p>

            <p>NANCE: What was the number of the <objectName type="gun">bullet</objectName> that was
               found? </p>

            <p>ZIEGLER: I understand that it was a <objectName type="gun">.38</objectName>. I
               haven't seen it.</p>

            <p>THE CORONER: That is all, you may be excused. That is all the <objectName type = 'evidence'>evidence</objectName> we will take in this <eventName type="case">case</eventName>. All but the
               <persName key="jury" ref='#legal' role ='unknown'>Jury</persName> will be excused. </p>
            <p>I hereby certify that I, as a <persName key="allen" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>shorthand reporter</persName>,
               correctly took down in <objectName type="evidence">shorthand</objectName> the <eventName
                  type="case">testimony and proceedings</eventName> had at the within named
               <persName key="allen" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>Coroner's</persName>
               <eventName type="case">inquest</eventName>; that the foregoing is a full, true and
               correct copy of my <objectName type="evidence">shorthand</objectName>
               <objectName type="document">notes</objectName> and a full, true and correct statement
               of <eventName type="case">the testimony and proceedings</eventName> had at said
               <eventName type="case">inquest</eventName>. <persName key="allen" ref='#law_enforcement' role ='unknown'>E.M.
                  Allen</persName>, <objectName type="evidence">Shorthand</objectName> Reporter </p>
            <p> _____ </p>

            <p>DETECTIVE STATEMENTS</p>

            <p>MR. CAHILL: We <eventName type="case">tested </eventName>that and the <objectName
                  type="gun">bullet</objectName> --- the <objectName type="gun">gun</objectName> was
               not more than an inch away from <persName key="taylor" ref='#director'>his body</persName> and they
               couldn't possibly get that close. </p>
            <p>MR. WOOLWINE: I heard it was 2 to 4 inches.</p>

            <p>MR. CAHILL: No, we have got it to within an inch, the <objectName type="evidence"
                  >test</objectName> shows that.</p>

            <p>MR. WINN: In my opinion, the <objectName type="gun">shot</objectName> that was fired
               4 inches from the <objectName type="clothing">pants</objectName> in making
                  that<eventName type="case"> demonstration</eventName>, is the nearest likeness to
               the <objectName type="gun">shot</objectName> in the <objectName type="clothing"
                  >coat</objectName>. </p>

